<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shameless" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shameless,</orth> wanting shame, insensible to disgrace, impudent: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.120" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.145" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.156" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 156</bibl>. Adverbially: <cit><quote>the wrong that she hath s. thrown on me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 202</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>grew s. desperate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 58</bibl></cit> (M. Edd. <emph>shameless-desperate</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>